  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Microcirculation, especially skin microcirculation, is a window towards systemic vascular
      function in magnitude and underlying mechanisms. Different techniques have been developed to
      assess the microcirculation. Among these techniques, laser technology is used to perform
      non-invasive microvascular assessments. Although this technique is widely used, different
      methodological issues remain. This study aims at defining the way to use lasers for clinical
      use.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
